<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="975" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d975">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Duarte</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-07-27"><hi rend="italic">July 27,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 87.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 21st instant, informing me of the deposit of
                            the money awarded by the Delagoa Bay arbitration.</p>
                        <p>As heretofore stated, the Government of the United States is not to be
                            understood as authorizing or acquiescing in the making of said deposit,
                            and in acknowledging the same it does so without prejudice and with
                            reservation of all its rights, of whatever nature or character they may
                            be, in the premises.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>